==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peripatetic
<hw>Per`i*pa*tet"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peripateticus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to walk about;
<grk>peri`</grk> about + <?/ to walk: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧ripat⟦eacute⟧tique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Walking
about; itinerant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the philosophy taught by
Aristotle (who gave his instructions while walking in the Lyceum at
Athens), or to his followers.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The true
<xex>peripatetic</xex> school.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peripatetic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peripatetic
<hw>Per`i*pa*tet"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who walks
about; a pedestrian; an itinerant.</def> <rj><au>Tatler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A disciple of Aristotle; an Aristotelian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peripatetical</ent>⟦br⟧
